<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-10-14T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-10-14T14:00:00-05:00" n="229" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d229">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">560.M5/150: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-10-14T14:00:00-05:00">October 14, 1930—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>98. Legation’s telegram 96, October 9, 10 a.m.<note n="53" xml:id="d229fn53">Not printed; see despatch No. 1692, October 9, <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi></note> Express to Secretary General
                            appreciation of offer of facilities and advise him that American Consul
                            at Geneva will be instructed to follow the proceedings. Inform
                            Gilbert.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
